        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/{size}/43780_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-07-20T17:31:47.132Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"navid-zamani\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"54537\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/navid-zamani/48/31913_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> navid-zamani:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I will have to check if it really gave a grace period</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>They really do. It looks like it is maybe about a week, given <a href=\"https://github.com/signalapp/Signal-Android/issues/12943\">this recently closed issue</a>. GitHub makes it near impossible to see actual timestamps on mobile, so all I can see is that it was marked as stale ‚Äúlast week‚Äù and then closed ‚Äúyesterday‚Äù:</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/6/6/66a56fa55c7eeab8c459ad5305452158126fa3a0.png\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/66a56fa55c7eeab8c459ad5305452158126fa3a0\" title=\"Screenshot_20230720-122718\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/6/6/66a56fa55c7eeab8c459ad5305452158126fa3a0_2_400x499.png\" alt=\"Screenshot_20230720-122718\" data-base62-sha1=\"eE397XrgDubEsmX9FftYGCf2POo\" width=\"400\" height=\"499\" srcset=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/6/6/66a56fa55c7eeab8c459ad5305452158126fa3a0_2_400x499.png, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/6/6/66a56fa55c7eeab8c459ad5305452158126fa3a0_2_600x748.png 1.5x, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/6/6/66a56fa55c7eeab8c459ad5305452158126fa3a0_2_800x998.png 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"343941\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">Screenshot_20230720-122718</span><span class=\"informations\">1152√ó1437 164 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"navid-zamani\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"54537\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/navid-zamani/48/31913_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> navid-zamani:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Yes, but I‚Äôm not an ‚Äúold person‚Äù, so I don‚Äôt use e-mail, so I only check them once a week</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Email definitely isn‚Äôt an ‚Äúold person‚Äù thing. It is still used for a large number of things, including important notifications from multiple services that even ‚Äúyoung people‚Äù use. There is no reason to ‚Äúcheck‚Äù it if you have a mobile device capable of receiving notifications; you simply see that you have a new email notification from GitHub (or whatever other service).</p>",
