        "cooked": "<p>Well, I may have been misunderstood. :) I put ‚Äúold person‚Äù in quotes as a joke, but didn‚Äôt say why.</p>\n<p>I‚Äôm the kind of guy who still uses IRC, knows Usenet and the Jargon File, has UDP over port 443 (aka QUIC) blocked to fight Google monopolizing the Internet, writes a ‚Äúbrowser killer‚Äù based on Linux KVM and also an alternative shell / user space for Linux (and a ‚Äúmobile device‚Äù killer), and despises any ‚Äúmodern‚Äù (but actually degenerated and backwards) ‚Äúsolution‚Äù (like non-federating instant messengers or bad re-inventions of existing technology due to incompetence [e.g. Discord, WhatsApp, or literally anything with Web- in front.]) ‚Ä¶ in favor of <em>actually</em> (still) modern stuff (like 9P‚Äô).</p>\n<p>I merely tried to hint at it really being weird that we don‚Äôt have an universal messaging system for any form of message (chat, letter, voice/video conferencing, publishing/blogging, etc) by now, and being my current favorite ‚Äúnew‚Äù candidate for that task. :)<br>\nAnd that is what makes e-mail the ‚Äúold‚Äù thing for me.<br>\nDefinitely absolutely not any of those toxic faux-‚Äúmodern‚Äù things coming out of silly con valley [sic]. ^^</p>\n<p>[Sorry, I had to say it.]</p>\n<p>Anyway, thank you for all your efforts and for caring. It‚Äôs people like you that give humanity any justification for existing at all. :)</p>",
