        "created_at": "2025-08-05T06:00:02.939Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I have this problem as well, and it is worse than described:</p>\n<p>This bug: <a href=\"https://github.com/signalapp/Signal-Android/issues/13477#issuecomment-2653075625\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Persistent notification \"group members have the same name\" ¬∑ Issue #13477 ¬∑ signalapp/Signal-Android ¬∑ GitHub</a> was closed even though there was activity (my comment) after it was marked stale/wontfix.</p>\n<p>Furthering the problem, I don‚Äôt have permission to reopen the bug. I am however allowed to open a new bug - how does this make sense?</p>\n<p>I recommend this article on the subject: <a href=\"https://jacobtomlinson.dev/posts/2024/most-stale-bots-are-anti-user-and-anti-contributor-but-they-dont-have-to-be/\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Most stale bots are anti-user and anti-contributor, but they don't have to be - Jacob Tomlinson</a></p>\n<p>Also: <a href=\"https://github.com/pouchdb/pouchdb/issues/8044\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Have Stalebot mark things as stale instead of wontfix ¬∑ Issue #8044 ¬∑ pouchdb/pouchdb ¬∑ GitHub</a> might be a helpful change to implement.</p>",
